      "writtenOn": "2018-03-01T21:09:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "eh, this looks messy... Also, after I thought over my previous advice of not caring about +w bit for old package, I now believe we should not change them. Let\u0027s handle this as a change in the format of the CIPD file. Current version v1 is \"+w bit in zip files is totally ignored regardless of what it is set to\". New version v1.1 will be \"+w bit in zip files is always respected\" (and we will set it to either +0200 or not when building the package). \n\nSo:\n1. Bump manifest version to \"1.1\": https://github.com/luci/luci-go/blob/master/cipd/client/cipd/local/json_descs.go#L37\n2. Do here\n\n  mode :\u003d os.FileMode(0400)\n  if in.Writable() {\n    mode |\u003d 0200\n  }\n\n3. In packageInstance.open read the version from the manifest, and forcefully remove 0222 if it is \u003d\u003d \"1\": https://github.com/luci/luci-go/blob/master/cipd/client/cipd/local/reader.go#L427\n\nWdyt?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 145,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 151,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "4252d5937f6525e518958c9387fbab289d3e548a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
